to the editor what is most remarkable in your feb 9 news article about the impact of the economic downturn on public attitudes toward protecting open space and insisting on smart growth rather than sprawl is how little evidence you found of a backlash in habersham county ga the voters this fall elected a slow growth county commission in erie colo developers spent a fortune trying to unseat mayor barbara connors and failed in loudon county va speculators who were n't able to win their case in the court of public opinion are turning to the courts while land use lawyers and real estate interests are as always eagerly proclaiming that bad times for americans are good times for sprawl the american people appear quite sensibly to be insisting that growth be smart planned and good for them and their families not just profitable for speculators carl pope executive director sierra club san francisco feb 11 2003

